<TITLE> Larma gets bail in attempted murder case </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, March 17 (bdnews24.com)The High Court Tuesday granted two months' anticipatory bail to Jyotirindra Bodhipriaya Larma, popularly known as Santu Larma, and 14 others in an attempted murder case. The court simultaneously ruled on the government to show cause within two weeks as to why Larma, the Parbatya Chattagram Jana Sanghati Samity (PCJSS) chief, should not be given permanent bail. On February 25, Chandra Shekhar Chakma, former general secretary of the hill council, filed the case against 15 people including Larma with Kotwali police in Rangamati. The case statement accused the 15 of a murder attempt on the complainant. Advocate AF Hassan Ariff, former law adviser to the past caretaker government, represented Larma. bdnew
